    <h1>Custom Cursor with Kursor.js</h1>

    <p>This project integrates <strong>Kursor.js</strong>, a lightweight JavaScript library for adding custom cursors to websites.</p>

    <h2>üöÄ Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Customizable cursor styles</li>
        <li>Lightweight and easy to implement</li>
        <li>Supports different cursor effects</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>üìå Installation</h2>

    <h3>1Ô∏è‚É£ Add Kursor.js via CDN</h3>
    <p>Insert the following lines into your HTML file inside the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> section:</p>
    
    <pre><code>&lt;!-- Kursor.js CSS --&gt;
&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="https://unpkg.com/kursor/dist/kursor.css"&gt;

&lt;!-- Kursor.js JavaScript --&gt;
&lt;script src="https://unpkg.com/kursor/dist/kursor.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>

    <h3>2Ô∏è‚É£ Initialize Kursor.js</h3>
    <p>Place this script before the closing <code>&lt;/body&gt;</code> tag:</p>

    <pre><code>&lt;script&gt;
  new kursor({
    type: 1,
    color: '#000000',
    removeDefaultCursor: false,
  });
&lt;/script&gt;
</code></pre>

    <h2>üé® Cursor Types</h2>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Effect</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>1</code></td>
            <td>Basic cursor</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>2</code></td>
            <td>Bouncing cursor</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>3</code></td>
            <td>Blurred effect</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>4</code></td>
            <td>Growth cursor</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>5</code></td>
            <td>Ring cursor</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h2>‚öôÔ∏è Customization Options</h2>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>Option</th>
            <th>Description</th>
            <th>Default Value</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>type</code></td>
            <td>Cursor effect type (1-5)</td>
            <td><code>1</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>color</code></td>
            <td>Cursor color (HEX)</td>
            <td><code>#000000</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><code>removeDefaultCursor</code></td>
            <td>Hide default browser cursor (<code>true</code> / <code>false</code>)</td>
            <td><code>false</code></td>
        </tr>
    </table>

